\\\"Fields per shift: employee name, date, hours\\\",\\\"Ability to add new shifts from the dashboard\\\",\\\"Persistent storage of shifts in a CMS collection\\\"]}\",\"version\":\"1.0\",\"summary\":\"Create a dedicated dashboard page for store owners to manage employee shifts, backed by a data collection that stores each shift record. The dashboard page displays shifts in a table (employee name, date, hours) and allows adding new shifts, which are persisted to the collection for ongoing management.\",\"id\":\"0144d7ba-ee15-44ef-86b7-4cc1507ac94f\"},\"config\":{\"borderless\":true,\"readAloud\":\"Welcome to ShiftCommand, your tool for managing employee shifts with ease. Here’s what you can do: The Shift Manager dashboard page displays a table of all employee shifts, showing details like the employee name, the shift date, and the number of hours worked. From this dashboard, you can also add new shift records directly. All shift data is stored in the Employee Shifts Data collection, ensuring that your records are saved and accessible for ongoing management. To get started, you can say things like, \\\"Show me the shift table,\\\" or \\\"Add a new shift.\\\" Let me know how I can assist you!\",\"textOnly\":\"Shift Manager is an admin dashboard page designed for store owners to manage employee shifts efficiently. The dashboard displays a table containing all shift records, including fields for employee name, shift date, and hours worked. Store owners can view existing shifts and add new shift records, which are stored persistently in the Employee Shifts Data collection for ongoing management. This ensures accurate tracking and organization of employee work schedules.\",\"userLanguage\":\"en\"}}>>"
