{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781087777222,"sessionID":"ses_14ee58b2fffeP6pDsoVmcnH3I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_01N86j594u2RZ9c5BEWRjgSz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/root/.agents/skills/wix-app/references/CODE_QUALITY.md"},"output":"<path>/root/.agents/skills/wix-app/references/CODE_QUALITY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Code Quality Requirements\n2: \n3: Applies to all generated code across every Wix CLI app extension type. Each per-extension reference links here instead of restating these rules.\n4: \n5: ## TypeScript Quality Guidelines\n6: \n7: - Generated code MUST compile with zero TypeScript errors under strict settings: `strict`, `noImplicitAny`, `strictNullChecks`, `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`.\n8: - Prefer type-narrowing and exhaustive logic over assertions; avoid non-null assertions (`!`) and unsafe casts (`as any`).\n9: - Treat optional values, refs, and array indexing results as possibly undefined and handle them explicitly.\n10: - Use exhaustive checks for unions (e.g., `switch` with a `never` check) and return total values (no implicit `undefined`).\n11: - Do NOT use `// @ts-ignore` or `// @ts-expect-error`; fix the types or add guards instead.\n12: \n13: ## Core Principles\n14: \n15: - Do NOT invent or assume new types, modules, functions, props, events, or imports. Use only entities present in the provided references or standard libraries already used in this project.\n16: - NEVER use mocks, placeholders, or TODOs in shipped code. ALWAYS implement complete, production-ready functionality.\n17: - If a required API, type, or module is missing, surface it to the user explicitly rather than inserting placeholder code.\n18: - Do NOT create README.md, CHANGELOG.md, or other unprompted markdown documentation — only output the files the task actually requires.\n19: \n20: ## Code Quality Standards\n21: \n22: - Add documentation only for complex or non-obvious logic — well-named identifiers should carry the rest.\n23: - Prefer `async`/`await` for asynchronous operations.\n24: \n25: ## Modular Code\n26: \n27: - If a generated file would exceed ~300 lines, split it into multiple smaller files with imports. Each component or function should stay ~50–100 lines.\n28: - Extract utilities/helpers into separate files; put types/interfaces into dedicated type files.\n29: - **Exception — auto-patterns override files** (column / action / slot / section / component / header overrides) ALWAYS live in their own file under `components/<type>/` with a `use*` hook, **regardless of file size**. This is a structural requirement of the override-registration model, not a size-based split — the ~300-line rule does NOT license inlining an override into the page component, even for a single small one. See [AUTO_PATTERNS_DASHBOARD.md](AUTO_PATTERNS_DASHBOARD.md).\n30: \n31: ## Error Handling\n32: \n33: - Log errors with `console.error` for debugging.\n34: - Handle network timeouts and external service failures.\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Code Quality Requirements\n\nApplies to all generated code across every Wix CLI app extension type. Each per-extension reference links here instead of restating these rules.\n\n## TypeScript Quality Guidelines\n\n- Generated code MUST compile with zero TypeScript errors under strict settings: `strict`, `noImplicitAny`, `strictNullChecks`, `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`.\n- Prefer type-narrowing and exhaustive logic over assertions; avoid non-null assertions (`!`) and unsafe casts (`as any`).\n- Treat optional values, refs, and array indexing results as possibly undefined and handle them explicitly.\n- Use exhaustive checks for unions (e.g., `switch` with a `never` check) and return total values (no implicit `undefined`).\n- Do NOT use `// @ts-ignore` or `// @ts-expect-error`; fix the types or add guards instead.\n\n## Core Principles\n\n- Do NOT invent or assume new types, modules, functions, props, events, or imports. Use only entities present in the provided references or standard libraries already used in this project.\n- NEVER use mocks, placeholders, or TODOs in shipped code. ALWAYS implement complete, production-ready functionality.\n- If a required API, type, or module is missing, surface it to the user explicitly rather than inserting placeholder code.\n- Do NOT create README.md, CHANGELOG.md, or other unprompted markdown documentation — only output the files the task actually requires.\n\n## Code Quality Standards","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"../root/.agents/skills/wix-app/references/CODE_QUALITY.md","time":{"start":1781087777198,"end":1781087777220}},"metadata":{"anthropic":{"caller":{"type":"direct"}}},"id":"prt_eb11aafb3001Pv2tKYb5elgpAh","sessionID":"ses_14ee58b2fffeP6pDsoVmcnH3I0","messageID":"msg_eb11aa2fd001wCBAYbfcz9WxFe"}}
