{"type":"text","timestamp":1781087963344,"sessionID":"ses_14ee58b2fffeP6pDsoVmcnH3I0","part":{"id":"prt_eb11d74ec0010r0H78npBuG0V6","messageID":"msg_eb11d6ebb001L46WoZA5bEizWS","sessionID":"ses_14ee58b2fffeP6pDsoVmcnH3I0","type":"text","text":"## Implementation Complete\n\nA **Shift Manager** dashboard page backed by an **Employee Shifts Data** CMS collection. Store owners can view all shifts in a table (employee name, date, hours) and add, edit, and delete shift records directly from the dashboard.\n\n**Extensions Created:**\n- `Shift Manager` — Auto-patterns dashboard page at `/shift-manager` with full CRUD for shift records\n- `Employee Shifts Data` — CMS collection (`@mirivo/my-appbw7bhj/employee-shifts`) with fields: `employeeName` (TEXT), `shiftDate` (DATE), `hours` (NUMBER)\n\n**Build Status:**\n- TypeScript: No compilation errors\n- Build: Completed successfully\n\n---\n\n## Manual Steps Required\n\n### 1. Add App Permissions in Dev Center\n\nThe dashboard page reads and writes the CMS collection at runtime. You must add these two scopes in [Dev Center → your app → Permissions](https://manage.wix.com/apps/dev-center-permissions):\n\n- `SCOPE.DC-DATA.READ`\n- `SCOPE.DC-DATA.WRITE`\n\nWithout these, the shift table will render but all data operations will fail.","time":{"start":1781087958252,"end":1781087963343}}}
